are yours and mine ♪

01:10.470 --> 01:11.870
♪ These happy days are yours ♪

01:12.005 --> 01:14.031
<i>♪ And mine, Happy Days! I</i>

01:17.744 --> 01:21.340
Happy Days is <i>filmed</i>
before a studio audience.

01:21.481 --> 01:24.041
RALPH: Please, Fonz, please!
We've got an emergency here,

01:24.184 --> 01:25.618
my car's got a dead battery,

01:25.752 --> 01:27.482
so we thought
maybe we could hook up

01:27.621 --> 01:28.679
the cables to Al's truck.

01:28.822 --> 01:30.119
Yeah, please, Fonz,
we need the car.

01:30.257 --> 01:31.884
We're taking the Drinkwater
twins to the drive-in.

01:32.025 --> 01:34.051
Oh, yeah?
Well, then why don't you hook up

01:34.194 --> 01:35.787
-the Drinkwater twins?
-(all laugh)

01:35.929 --> 01:39.160
It's funny working with him!

01:39.299 --> 01:40.630
All right, take the cables.

01:40.767 --> 01:42.736
- You just bring 'em back
tonight. -Oh, thanks, Fonz!

01:42.869 --> 01:44.997
All right, they're under there
over the table, by the table.

01:45.138 --> 01:46.231
- You can trust us.
- Yeah. -Thanks, Fonz, thanks.

01:46.373 --> 01:48.671
- Hey.
- No touch, no touch.

01:48.809 --> 01:51.403
- RALPH: Hi, Lori.
- POTSIE: Hi, Lori.

01:56.083 --> 01:59.212
I'd like to introduce to you,
the Wild One himself,

01:59.353 --> 02:02.379
Richie "Wheelie" Cunningham!

02:02.522 --> 02:03.888
Bravo!

02:04.024 --> 02:05.514
Yeah!

02:07.127 --> 02:08.890
You got a bike!

02:09.029 --> 02:10.588
Hey, Rich, Rich,
this is a beaut!

02:10.731 --> 02:11.925
Yeah, isn't it neat?

02:12.065 --> 02:14.534
I just brought it down here
so Fonz could, you know,

02:14.668 --> 02:16.261
check it out,
give me a few tips.

02:16.403 --> 02:18.462
He's gonna love this!
It's the best bike in Milwaukee.

02:18.605 --> 02:20.869
(clanking)

02:21.008 --> 02:23.602
And, Fonz,
uh, what do you think?

02:23.744 --> 02:24.938
It's-it's nice, huh?

02:25.078 --> 02:27.570
First of all, bikes
are not nice, they're cool.

02:27.714 --> 02:30.047
Second of all, you want
to be a big leaguer,

02:30.183 --> 02:31.708
you talk like the big leagues.

02:31.852 --> 02:33.547
Right, Fonz. Well, it is cool.

02:33.687 --> 02:35.849
- I should have done this
a long time ago. -Yeah, yeah.

02:35.989 --> 02:38.117
Richie Cunningham with a bike.

02:38.258 --> 02:40.386
Well, I guess Milwaukee's
big enough for two Fonzies.

02:40.527 --> 02:42.427
There's only one Fonz.
Right, Chach?

02:42.562 --> 02:44.155
- Right, Ralph.
- We were just leaving, Fonz.

02:44.297 --> 02:46.232
- Nice bike, Rich. See you.
- Yeah, great bike, Rich.

02:46.366 --> 02:48.027
No, no, bikes are cool,
they're not nice!

02:48.168 --> 02:49.226
Cool, cool.

02:49.369 --> 02:50.666
Thanks again
for the cables, Fonz.

02:50.804 --> 02:51.896
Follow those clowns,

02:52.039 --> 02:53.973
make sure they don't knot up
my cables, huh?

02:54.107 --> 02:55.632
Right, Fonz. Oh, uh, I forgot.

02:55.776 --> 02:56.674
Rochelle called before.

02:56.810 --> 03:00.075
Rochelle.

03:00.213 --> 03:03.149
What a beauty mark.

03:03.283 --> 03:04.774
I never saw a beauty mark.

03:04.918 --> 03:08.047
And you never will.

03:08.188 --> 03:11.886
Fonz, uh, how'd you like
to double on motorcycles?

03:12.025 --> 03:14.927
Hey, great. Leather's in
the office. We'll triple-date.

03:15.062 --> 03:18.088
Well, Chachi, I doubt if Leather
wants to ride on a motorcycle

03:18.231 --> 03:19.563
that has training wheels.

03:19.700 --> 03:20.724
(laughs)

03:20.867 --> 03:22.528
He's a kid, training wheels...

03:22.669 --> 03:24.694
It's not easy being
second mechanic.

03:24.838 --> 03:26.863
- The cables.
- Right, Fonz.

03:27.007 --> 03:28.839
All right.

03:28.975 --> 03:30.273
Want your first lesson?

03:30.410 --> 03:31.400
- Yeah.
- Man your bike.

03:31.545 --> 03:34.639
Oh, right. Hop on, L.B.

03:34.781 --> 03:37.444
L.B., the owner gets on first.

03:37.584 --> 03:39.780
Oh, yeah.

03:39.920 --> 03:41.513
Where should I put my hands?

03:41.655 --> 03:44.021
Oh, just, uh, keep looking.

03:45.025 --> 03:46.117
How's this?

03:46.259 --> 03:47.591
Oh, yeah, that's cute,
that's cute, okay.

03:47.728 --> 03:50.663
Okay, I'm gonna start it,
uh, key's on,

03:50.797 --> 03:53.926
I, I already got it in neutral.
Here we go.

03:55.035 --> 03:56.901
Not so good, Richie.

03:57.037 --> 03:59.403
No, no, I'll get it,
I'll get it. It's...

03:59.539 --> 04:02.532
Hey.

04:02.676 --> 04:04.872
Do-si-do, and around you go...

04:08.081 --> 04:10.414
We're not doing square dances
here, you understand that?

04:10.550 --> 04:12.075
All right, now assume
it started.

04:12.219 --> 04:13.311
- Oh, all right.
- All right.

04:13.453 --> 04:16.446
(makes revving sounds)

04:18.358 --> 04:21.089
Cunningham... I think you're,

04:21.228 --> 04:22.456
you're exceeding
the speed limit here.

04:22.596 --> 04:23.790
Oh, yeah.

04:23.930 --> 04:25.899
- Now, you're just cruising
down the street. -Right.

04:26.032 --> 04:28.001
Here comes a stop sign.
What are you gonna do?

04:28.135 --> 04:29.534
Okay, uh, here comes
a stop sign,

04:29.669 --> 04:31.365
I'm going to, uh,
put on the brake

04:31.505 --> 04:32.665
and screech to a halt.

04:32.806 --> 04:34.865
(makes screech sound)

04:35.008 --> 04:36.066
(engine idling sound)

04:37.310 --> 04:39.301
- Now what?
- Well, now the cop comes up

04:39.446 --> 04:40.914
and gives you a ticket

04:41.047 --> 04:42.310
'cause you just pulled
the clutch

04:42.449 --> 04:43.939
and went right through
the stop sign.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.517
What, that-that's the clutch?

04:45.652 --> 04:47.484
That's right. Here's your brake
right here.

04:47.621 --> 04:49.851
Son of a gun, you know
they look exactly alike?

04:49.990 --> 04:52.151
How are you supposed
to know which is which?

04:52.292 --> 04:53.782
Well, one'll kill ya.

04:53.927 --> 04:56.294
It'll be good
if I remember that.

04:56.429 --> 04:57.863
Yeah.

04:57.998 --> 05:00.558
Hey, gang.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.398
- Hi, Leather. -Hi, Leather.
- How you doing?

05:05.539 --> 05:07.837
I just talked to my agent.
I got a gig tonight.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.567
- Oh, that's great. -That's
great. -Hey, that's great.

05:09.709 --> 05:11.405
Oh, wow, Fonzie,
you got a new bike.

05:11.545 --> 05:12.478
Hold it.

05:12.612 --> 05:14.478
The Fonz don't get a new bike.

05:14.614 --> 05:17.482
Do you think the Lone Ranger
would trade in his Silver?

05:17.617 --> 05:19.552
No, no, no, this is my bike.

05:19.686 --> 05:22.917
All 650cc's of it.

05:23.056 --> 05:24.683
That's motorcycle talk.

05:24.825 --> 05:27.521
(horn beeps)

05:27.661 --> 05:30.187
That's horn talk.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.729
Listen, Fonz,
the gig is in Waukegan.

05:31.865 --> 05:33.594
Can you give me a lift
to the bus?

05:33.733 --> 05:35.065
- Oh, sure.
- Oh, great.

05:35.202 --> 05:38.729
And then I'll meet Rochelle and
play "Connect the beauty marks."

05:38.872 --> 05:39.737
- Fonz.
- Yeah.

05:39.873 --> 05:41.170
I think I'm gonna take this out

05:41.308 --> 05:42.798
for just a little spin
around the block

05:42.943 --> 05:44.206
before you look it over.
Is that all right?

05:44.344 --> 05:45.573
Yeah, that's cool.
All right, just take it slow.

05:45.712 --> 05:47.077
- Right.
- All right?

05:47.214 --> 05:48.579
I'll be back, we'll spend
a couple of hours together,

05:48.715 --> 05:49.910
you'll be zooming down that road
in no time.

05:50.050 --> 05:52.746
- Oh, that's gonna be great.
-(horn beeps)

05:52.886 --> 05:55.378
The first thing we do when I get
back: disconnect the horn.

05:55.522 --> 05:56.387
Thanks.

05:56.523 --> 05:58.082
See you later, huh?

05:58.225 --> 05:59.214
- Yeah.
- Bye, Fonz.

05:59.359 --> 06:00.349
- Now, you on?
- Yeah.

06:00.493 --> 06:01.586
Okay,

06:01.728 --> 06:03.719
I got past the first part
of getting the bike.

06:03.863 --> 06:05.593
Now I got to get past
the second part,

06:05.732 --> 06:06.858
telling my folks about it.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.229
You didn't tell
your parents yet?

06:08.368 --> 06:09.597
Don't worry.

06:09.736 --> 06:11.568
Wheelie Cunningham
will win 'em over.

06:14.474 --> 06:16.374
Oh, hi, everybody.

06:16.509 --> 06:18.978
- HOWARD: Richard.
- MARION: Hi, Richard.

06:19.112 --> 06:22.742
Hi. Oh, man,
I'm really glad to be home.

06:22.882 --> 06:25.215
Mom, you're really looking good
tonight.

06:25.352 --> 06:27.411
What-- did you do something
to your hair?

06:27.554 --> 06:28.680
Uh-uh, no.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.756
Oh, well,
it's just beautiful. It's...

06:30.890 --> 06:33.485
Dad... Dad...

06:33.627 --> 06:36.152
how was your day
at the store, huh?

06:36.296 --> 06:38.924
Hey, Joanie. Hey,
cute daughter you got there.

06:39.065 --> 06:40.465
You know something, Dad?

06:40.600 --> 06:43.126
You have done an excellent job
raising this whole family.

06:43.270 --> 06:45.795
All right, Richard,
what do you want?

06:45.939 --> 06:47.600
What do I want?

06:47.741 --> 06:49.709
Oh, no, I-l don't want anything.

06:49.843 --> 06:52.243
I'm just full of love tonight.

06:52.379 --> 06:53.903
You're full of something.

06:55.682 --> 06:57.582
Mom, what are we having
for dinner, huh?

06:57.717 --> 06:58.810
You know,
I'll tell you something.

06:58.952 --> 07:01.648
Nobody makes a dinner
like my mom.

07:01.788 --> 07:04.223
- Peanut butter.
- Peanut butter?

07:04.357 --> 07:07.020
Oh, good, good,
I love peanut butter.

07:07.160 --> 07:08.423
Your father ate all the chops.

07:08.561 --> 07:10.154
That's okay, Dad.
I would have given them

07:10.297 --> 07:11.457
to you if I had been here.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.499
Now let's stop this nonsense.

07:14.634 --> 07:16.068
Now tell us what happened, huh?

07:16.202 --> 07:18.694
All right, all right.

07:18.838 --> 07:20.272
I, uh...

07:20.407 --> 07:23.399
(muttering):
I got a motorcycle.

07:23.543 --> 07:24.533
(clears throat)

07:24.678 --> 07:25.838
What, Richard?
I didn't hear you.

07:25.979 --> 07:27.378
I, I just said that I...

07:27.514 --> 07:30.142
(mumbling):
...got a motorcycle.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.684
Will you take your hand away
from your mouth?!

07:32.819 --> 07:34.014
It sounded like you said,

07:34.154 --> 07:36.350
-"I just bought a motorcycle."
- I got a motorcycle.

07:36.489 --> 07:39.550
Well, Richard, y-you should have
asked us first!

07:39.693 --> 07:41.388
That is out of the question!

07:41.528 --> 07:44.395
Now wait a minute.
I think this is pretty unfair.

07:44.531 --> 07:46.624
You know, I'm always being
treated like a kid around here.

07:46.766 --> 07:48.427
Join the club.

07:48.568 --> 07:49.865
- All right, you want fair?
- Yeah.

07:50.003 --> 07:51.493
You give me one good reason

07:51.638 --> 07:53.436
why we should let you have
a motorcycle.

07:53.573 --> 07:55.303
That's easy.
It's very cheap on gas.

07:55.442 --> 07:57.467
- Good point.
- Thanks, Joanie.

07:57.610 --> 08:00.170
But it evens out
with medical bills.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.839
- Will you go to your room?
- Okay, okay.

08:02.982 --> 08:05.144
If you don't want my advice...

08:05.285 --> 08:07.219
Why do you want a motorcycle?

08:07.354 --> 08:08.412
All right, number two,

08:08.555 --> 08:10.284
it's always easy
to find a parking space.

08:10.423 --> 08:12.323
All right, so it's cheap on gas

08:12.459 --> 08:14.859
and you can find
a parking space.

08:14.994 --> 08:16.360
But I absolutely forbid it!

08:16.496 --> 08:17.361
Good, Howard.

08:17.497 --> 08:18.692
"Forbid it"?

08:18.832 --> 08:20.129
"Good, Howard"?

08:20.266 --> 08:21.598
All right, all right,
all right, fine,

08:21.735 --> 08:23.293
you're gonna treat me
like a baby, I'll be a baby.

08:23.436 --> 08:24.870
You want a baby?
Here's a baby!

08:25.004 --> 08:27.132
<i>(subs)</i>

08:27.273 --> 08:28.741
HOWARD:
You want to be a baby?

08:28.875 --> 08:29.933
MARION:
I can't believe this!

08:30.076 --> 08:31.567
I've never seen you act
like this, Richard.

08:31.711 --> 08:34.304
(overlapping chatter)

08:34.447 --> 08:35.938
- That's terrible. -Spending
your own money like that.

08:36.082 --> 08:39.143
L-I love this,
my little stepfamily,

08:39.284 --> 08:42.187
full of spunk and vinegar,
you know.

08:42.322 --> 08:43.812
Here's my bottle of rent.

08:48.161 --> 08:51.324
I don't want to say anything,
but he's sucking his thumb.

08:51.464 --> 08:52.864
Yeah.

08:52.999 --> 08:54.160
That's right, that's right.

08:54.300 --> 08:56.792
They treat me like a baby,
so I'm gonna be a baby.

08:56.936 --> 08:58.461
I'm gonna suck my thumb.

09:00.173 --> 09:02.608
L-I don't think
I'm ever gonna understand

09:02.742 --> 09:04.733
a middle-class family.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.142
Arthur, now Richard is getting
a motorcycle,

09:07.280 --> 09:08.873
and we don't think it's safe.

09:09.015 --> 09:11.450
Now, Mrs. C., wait a minute.
I checked it out.

09:11.584 --> 09:14.076
He's a good driver,
it's in good shape, huh?

09:14.220 --> 09:17.884
Yeah, but it's my son's shape
that I'm worried about, Fonzie.

09:18.024 --> 09:19.321
You know, there are some people

09:19.459 --> 09:21.188
that should not ride
motorcycles.

09:21.327 --> 09:23.193
You know,
I totally agree with you.

09:23.329 --> 09:24.763
Potsie is a good example.

09:24.898 --> 09:26.058
And Richard, too.

09:26.199 --> 09:29.635
No, Richie wouldn't ride right
in the middle of a fruit stand.

09:29.769 --> 09:31.260
Potsie did that?

09:31.404 --> 09:32.804
Yeah. He hit head-on,

09:32.939 --> 09:34.805
right in the middle
of these, uh, honeydew melons.

09:34.941 --> 09:36.966
It took us about an hour
to find his head.

09:37.110 --> 09:39.545
(laughs)
That's funny.

09:39.679 --> 09:42.171
MARION:
Oh!

09:42.315 --> 09:43.612
You see, Richard?

09:43.750 --> 09:45.741
Even Arthur says it's dangerous.

09:45.885 --> 09:48.320
Oh, now wait a minute.
Fonzie did not say that.

09:48.455 --> 09:49.717
He said it's dangerous
for Potsie.

09:49.856 --> 09:51.085
Right.

09:51.224 --> 09:55.252
Walking is dangerous for Potsie.

09:55.395 --> 09:58.660
Now, look, Mr. C., Mrs. C.,
if it makes you feel any better,

09:58.798 --> 10:02.234
I checked out the bike,
I took Richie for a ride,

10:02.368 --> 10:04.735
he did very, very well, huh?

10:04.871 --> 10:06.100
Of course, I suggest

10:06.239 --> 10:08.401
he takes the thumb out
of his mouth, but...

10:08.541 --> 10:09.531
Well...

10:09.676 --> 10:12.202
Dad, Dad, look, I bought
the bike with money

10:12.345 --> 10:13.779
that I saved working
in the band.

10:13.913 --> 10:15.848
Now, you said
that I was old enough now,

10:15.982 --> 10:17.211
you said I was an adult.

10:17.350 --> 10:18.750
No, he just said
you were old enough

10:18.885 --> 10:20.080
to make your own decisions.

10:20.220 --> 10:23.246
Yeah! Well, that's my decision,
to buy a motorcycle.

10:23.389 --> 10:25.187
You're not old enough.

10:26.759 --> 10:29.558
Well, I did say
you were an adult, Richard,

10:29.696 --> 10:32.665
so I guess I at least have
to let you try it.

10:32.799 --> 10:34.631
Oh, thanks, Dad.

10:34.767 --> 10:35.894
Is your thumb dry?

10:36.035 --> 10:38.698
Oh. Will be, Will be.

10:38.838 --> 10:40.772
All right, all right,
there you go. That settles it.

10:40.907 --> 10:42.739
Now just do me a favor,
you take it nice and slow.

10:42.876 --> 10:43.740
All right.

10:43.877 --> 10:47.040
And you wear your helmet
and never smile.

10:48.081 --> 10:51.346
But never smile?
Why?

10:51.484 --> 10:53.748
'Cause you get bugs
in your teeth.

10:53.887 --> 10:56.651
(laughs)

10:56.789 --> 10:59.258
Bugs in your teeth...
I don't think it's very funny.

10:59.392 --> 11:01.759
Well, don't worry, Marion.

11:01.895 --> 11:03.522
If Fonzie gave him
some pointers,

11:03.663 --> 11:05.961
I'm sure he's gonna be
just fine.

11:06.099 --> 11:07.828
(motorcycle roars)

11:07.967 --> 11:09.298
(tires squeal,
motorcycle departs)

11:14.941 --> 11:17.603
Man, did you hear that?
Wasn't that terrific?

11:17.744 --> 11:20.372
I would never do that.

11:28.021 --> 11:30.421
That's it, Al, keep it turned.
A little more.

11:30.557 --> 11:31.854
Keep pushing, guys.

11:31.991 --> 11:33.084
Come on, Pots, push.

11:33.226 --> 11:34.955
We've got to get
to the drive-in.

11:35.094 --> 11:37.290
I am pushing.
Chach, why aren't you helping?

11:37.430 --> 11:40.161
Did you ever hear
of child labor laws?

11:40.300 --> 11:41.995
Boy, Pots, you should have
been more careful

11:42.135 --> 11:43.295
with that jumper cable.

11:43.436 --> 11:44.927
Put the fire out, didn't I?

11:45.071 --> 11:48.006
Boys, quit,
quit arguing and push!

11:48.141 --> 11:49.131
We're here, Al.

11:49.275 --> 11:51.209
Oh. Oh, yeah.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.472
(grunts)
Thanks, guys.

11:53.613 --> 11:58.448
Hey, you know, I had
the emergency brake on?

11:58.585 --> 12:01.247
For 20 blocks?

12:01.387 --> 12:03.413
It holds pretty good.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.786
Hey, Fonz! Fonzie!

12:05.925 --> 12:07.359
He's not here.

12:07.493 --> 12:10.088
You brought me to a garage
without a mechanic?

12:10.229 --> 12:12.221
- That's right.
- No sweat.

12:12.365 --> 12:14.060
Chachi, number two mechanic,
is on duty.

12:14.200 --> 12:16.396
Oh, Chachi,
promise me one thing.

12:16.536 --> 12:18.800
You won't take the truck apart
and sell it?

12:18.938 --> 12:21.134
How much do you think
we can get for it?

12:21.274 --> 12:23.436
That's funny.
Even tired, I got it.

12:23.576 --> 12:25.601
I think I know what's wrong
with it, Al.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.270
What a mess, what a mess.

12:27.413 --> 12:29.575
Oh, no problem, guys,
it's in good hands.

12:29.716 --> 12:33.618
Look, Pots, you had to hook
the cable to the carburetor?

12:34.887 --> 12:36.082
I can't believe it.

12:36.222 --> 12:38.122
We finally get a date
with the Drinkwater twins

12:38.257 --> 12:40.123
and we blow up two cars!

12:40.259 --> 12:41.625
(engine starts)

12:41.761 --> 12:43.024
(whooping, shouting)

12:43.162 --> 12:44.323
Drinkwater twins,
Drinkwater twins,

12:44.464 --> 12:46.330
- Drinkwater twins...
- Keep it going, keep it going...

12:46.466 --> 12:48.263
Help, somebody, help!

12:48.401 --> 12:49.300
What happened?

12:49.435 --> 12:50.664
- We crashed!
- What?

12:50.803 --> 12:52.032
- You crashed?
- Are you all right?

12:52.171 --> 12:53.798
Not me. Richie--
he's lying in the street.

12:53.940 --> 12:56.409
He's not moving,
he's not moving!

12:56.542 --> 12:58.101
- Come on!
- Let's go! -Let's go!

12:58.244 --> 12:59.507
- AL: Chachi...
- Let's go!

12:59.646 --> 13:01.637
