DOCTOR: Your son is
in critical condition.

13:22.402 --> 13:24.461
If he comes out of the coma soon
and regains consciousness,

13:24.604 --> 13:25.935
he should be all right.

13:26.973 --> 13:28.065
If?

13:28.207 --> 13:30.699
No, no, he-he-he didn't mean
"if," Marion,

13:30.843 --> 13:32.641
he meant when he comes
out of the coma.

13:32.779 --> 13:34.804
You-you meant "when,"
didn't you, Doc?

13:35.848 --> 13:38.181
He had a very bad fall,
Mr. Cunningham.

13:38.317 --> 13:39.808
We'll just have to wait and see.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.148
Dear God...

13:47.694 --> 13:50.163
It's a good thing
he was wearing his helmet.

13:50.296 --> 13:51.661
It could have been worse.

13:51.798 --> 13:53.595
Now there's...

13:53.733 --> 13:55.792
really nothing that
you people can do here.

13:55.935 --> 13:57.528
Why don't you just go home?

13:57.670 --> 13:59.661
Well, I-in just a minute.

14:05.044 --> 14:07.035
Oh, Howard, this is all
like a bad dream.

14:07.180 --> 14:09.478
All right now, sweetheart,
he-he's going to be all right.

14:09.615 --> 14:10.844
He's getting the best of care.

14:10.983 --> 14:12.975
Richie will be fine.

14:13.119 --> 14:14.712
Yeah.

14:14.854 --> 14:16.845
Come on, Mom.

14:19.959 --> 14:21.051
Oh, Arthur...

14:21.194 --> 14:22.252
Yeah, I know.

14:27.567 --> 14:29.091
Hi, Red.

14:31.137 --> 14:33.128
I'm right here with you.

14:35.041 --> 14:37.442
How is he?

14:37.577 --> 14:40.046
Well, he's...
not very good, Fonzie,

14:40.179 --> 14:42.842
but there is a chance.

14:42.982 --> 14:44.973
Is there anything I can do?

14:46.619 --> 14:47.518
Nothing.

14:47.653 --> 14:49.713
Come on, let's go home.

15:15.148 --> 15:16.843
<i>JQANE: Thanks for
coming over, everybody.</i>

15:16.983 --> 15:19.145
<i>AL: Let's have something to eat
while we're waiting.</i>

15:19.285 --> 15:21.686
MARION:
Here.

15:21.821 --> 15:23.084
- Oh, hi.
- Hi, Al. -Hi, Al.

15:23.222 --> 15:24.087
Any news?

15:24.223 --> 15:25.953
No change, so far.

15:26.092 --> 15:27.491
No, but he's going
to be all right.

15:27.627 --> 15:29.254
He's-he's a very tough kid.

15:29.395 --> 15:30.886
Sure he is.

15:31.030 --> 15:32.964
Well, I'm gonna
clean this house.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.897
Marion, you cleaned the house
this morning.

15:36.569 --> 15:39.163
Let's have some macaroni
and cheese, all right?

15:39.305 --> 15:40.864
<i>L-I'll</i> have a bite, Al.

15:41.007 --> 15:42.372
I could go for one helping.

15:42.508 --> 15:44.977
- Oh, kids, how they can eat.
- Yeah.

15:45.111 --> 15:47.944
I remember one time Richie...

15:53.986 --> 15:55.977
Changed my mind.
I'm not hungry.

15:58.491 --> 16:00.482
Now listen to me, everybody.

16:02.028 --> 16:03.689
Richard's been in an accident

16:03.830 --> 16:05.491
and he's been badly hurt.

16:05.631 --> 16:07.463
Okay, people get badly hurt

16:07.600 --> 16:09.466
and get sick every single day.

16:09.602 --> 16:11.297
The only thing is,

16:11.437 --> 16:12.871
we always think
it's only gonna happen

16:13.005 --> 16:14.371
to somebody else's family.

16:14.507 --> 16:16.168
Well, now it's happened to ours,

16:16.309 --> 16:18.607
and we have to deal with it.

16:18.744 --> 16:21.043
And right now
that's what I'm trying to do,

16:21.180 --> 16:23.342
and I say that Richard
is going to be all right.

16:23.482 --> 16:25.713
MARION:
Of course he is.

16:25.852 --> 16:27.319
And we're just very grateful

16:27.453 --> 16:29.820
that Richard has
friends that care.

16:33.626 --> 16:35.617
(playing quietly)

17:08.426 --> 17:10.419
<i>II</i>

17:36.689 --> 17:38.680
<i>II</i>

18:02.248 --> 18:04.239
(piano stops)

18:12.425 --> 18:14.416
His condition is stable.

18:14.560 --> 18:16.551
We'll just have to wait and see.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.718
How you doin', Red?

18:51.964 --> 18:54.365
They wouldn't let me stay
before, but I'm here now.

18:57.336 --> 19:00.272
Chachi says hello.
"Hello."

19:00.406 --> 19:02.704
He loves working down
at that garage, you know.

19:06.445 --> 19:08.812
You can't do this, uh, Red.

19:08.948 --> 19:10.677
A lot of people counting on you,
you know.

19:10.816 --> 19:14.343
Your mother,
your father, Joanie...

19:14.487 --> 19:16.478
Ralph, Potsie...

19:18.090 --> 19:19.114
You can't go yet,

19:19.258 --> 19:21.249
you got a whole lifetime
ahead of you, you know?

19:23.429 --> 19:24.589
I mean, you didn't even make

19:24.730 --> 19:26.130
the editor of that
college paper yet.

19:26.265 --> 19:28.199
There's a lot of...
crummy journalism around,

19:28.334 --> 19:30.325
you got to make it all straight.

19:31.637 --> 19:33.503
They need you.

19:33.639 --> 19:35.630
(scoffs)

19:41.580 --> 19:43.572
(choked up):
I need you.

19:45.985 --> 19:48.249
You're my best friend.

19:48.387 --> 19:51.050
I know I never said that before,
but I'm saying it now.

19:53.059 --> 19:55.960
You are my best friend.

19:56.095 --> 19:58.120
And I don't want to lose you.

20:06.972 --> 20:10.773
Hey, uh... sir?

20:10.910 --> 20:12.776
Got to have a little chat here.

20:12.912 --> 20:15.938
It's my best friend Richie.

20:16.082 --> 20:18.073
Now, he's in really bad shape.

20:19.985 --> 20:23.183
Yeah, I know you know that.

20:23.322 --> 20:26.087
But, uh, the world is kind of
going a little wacko, you know,

20:26.225 --> 20:28.592
and, uh, you need...

20:28.727 --> 20:31.856
you need people
down here like him.

20:31.997 --> 20:33.989
(sobbing):
And if you don't, I do.

20:37.036 --> 20:41.871
Now... I can fix a lot
of things, but, uh...

20:42.007 --> 20:44.602
this one is all yours.

20:44.743 --> 20:46.712
So, uh...

20:46.846 --> 20:48.438
let's make a little deal.

20:53.219 --> 20:56.882
You do this for me...

20:57.022 --> 20:59.014
and I'll owe you one.

21:00.392 --> 21:02.327
Heyyy.

21:02.461 --> 21:04.862
(sobbing)

21:23.682 --> 21:25.275
Will you look at that?

21:25.417 --> 21:27.147
He must have
stayed here all night.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.414
Fonzie? Fonzie.

21:31.991 --> 21:34.050
Arthur, it's morning.

21:34.193 --> 21:36.184
Have you been here all night?

21:36.328 --> 21:38.558
Yeah, I guess I fell asleep.

21:38.697 --> 21:40.359
Doctor said it was
all right, though.

21:40.499 --> 21:42.263
Well, you go home now.

21:42.401 --> 21:43.562
Go on home, Fonzie.

21:43.702 --> 21:45.364
We'll tell Richard
you were here.

21:45.504 --> 21:47.473
I don't think
I'm going to leave here.

21:47.606 --> 21:50.371
Well, Arthur, you just go home
now and get some sleep.

21:50.509 --> 21:51.772
Yeah, Marion's right.

21:51.911 --> 21:53.845
Yeah, you're both right,
but I ain't going.

21:53.979 --> 21:55.640
- We're going to stay here...
- Fonzie, it doesn't

21:55.781 --> 21:57.715
-do you any good...
- There's a lot of food at home.

21:57.850 --> 21:58.942
Why don't you just go?
We're gonna be here.

21:59.084 --> 22:00.313
