the speaker the whole time.

23:52.965 --> 23:54.398
(laughs)

23:56.435 --> 23:57.630
Let's get something to eat.

23:57.770 --> 23:59.328
I think they want to be alone.

23:59.471 --> 24:00.632
Yeah.

24:00.773 --> 24:02.866
I'll never forget this week.

24:03.008 --> 24:04.339
Well, Marion...

24:04.476 --> 24:06.911
no one said it was easy
being a parent.

24:07.046 --> 24:09.708
I know.

24:09.848 --> 24:11.840
But it can be so painful.

24:13.619 --> 24:15.849
I'm just going to walk Lori Beth
out to her car.

24:15.988 --> 24:17.148
Say good night for us, dear.

24:17.289 --> 24:18.882
Yeah.

24:19.024 --> 24:20.549
Say, uh...

24:20.693 --> 24:22.183
I-I guess I must have
put you through

24:22.328 --> 24:24.193
a lot this week and, uh...

24:24.330 --> 24:25.354
with the accident
and everything...

24:25.497 --> 24:26.988
Oh, don't worry about it,
Richard.

24:27.132 --> 24:28.600
It's all part of being a parent.

24:28.734 --> 24:29.758
Thanks.

24:29.902 --> 24:30.892
I'll see you.

24:31.036 --> 24:32.163
